---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import CtaBand from "../components/CtaBand.astro";
import { SITE } from "../config/site";
---

<Layout
  title="About Us"
  description="Midwest Waste Consultants is an owner-operated waste consulting and brokering firm with 30+ years in the field, based in the Illinois Fox Valley and serving clients nationwide."
>
  <section class="relative isolate overflow-hidden bg-navy">
    <img
      src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dsbllwpbh/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/mwc/images/photos/about-hero"
      alt="The Midwest Waste Consultants owners together at their Fox Valley yard"
      width="1600"
      height="900"
      fetchpriority="high"
      decoding="async"
      class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 h-full w-full object-cover object-right"
    />
    <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 bg-gradient-to-r from-navy-deep/95 via-navy-deep/80 to-navy-deep/30" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10 bg-gradient-to-t from-navy-deep/70 to-transparent" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-20 sm:py-28">
      <span class="eyebrow border-l-2 border-orange pl-3">About Us</span>
      <h1 class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-4xl font-extrabold leading-[1.08] text-white sm:text-5xl">
        Thirty years on the trucks. Now in your corner.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-xl text-lg text-white/80">
        We're not a national hauler with a friendly logo. We're the people who spent careers inside this industry — and decided to use what we learned for the customer instead of against them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 prose-mwc">
    <span class="eyebrow">Our Story</span>
    <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-extrabold text-navy">Owner-operated since {SITE.established}.</h2>
    <p class="text-muted">
      Midwest Waste Consultants was built on a simple frustration: businesses
      were getting buried by waste contracts written to confuse them. Auto-renewal
      clauses. Surcharges that appeared out of nowhere. Containers sized to bill
      more, not to fit the job. After 30+ years working in waste and hauling, we
      knew exactly where the money leaks — so we started a company to plug it.
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted">
      Today we do two things. Our trucks handle hands-on hauling and roll-off
      service across the Illinois Fox Valley — Sugar Grove, Aurora, and the
      surrounding communities. And our consulting and brokering practice works
      <em>nationally</em>, sourcing and negotiating service for businesses with one
      location or hundreds.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-extrabold text-navy">Meet the owners</h2>
    <p class="text-muted">
      Midwest Waste was born in a corporate office at a previous publicly-traded
      hauler — in the middle of a meeting about how to raise prices on customers
      outside their contracted terms. At the time, <strong>Greg</strong> was
      <strong>Tyler's</strong> sales manager. They looked at each other and said,
      "This is crazy — there has to be a better way." So they built it. Greg and
      Tyler are also family by marriage: their wives are first cousins, which means
      nothing goes unsaid and feelings get checked at the door.
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted">
      <strong>Greg Lower</strong> came up the hard way — from the back of a garbage
      truck to Vice President of the organization. Over the years he's helped
      hundreds of customers, and his reputation in the community is everything to
      him. Every interaction gets the same personable, straight-shooting treatment.
      Greg loves his family, his sports, and helping people.
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted">
      <strong>Tyler Weber</strong> followed Greg into waste and recycling after cutting
      his teeth in door-to-door sales. His competitive streak and tell-it-like-it-is
      style built a growing book of business across the Fox Valley — always trying
      to do more with less for the customer. Tyler loves his family, his golf, and
      helping people.
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted">
      Both of them know the Chicagoland waste market has forgotten what honest,
      upfront, consistent service looks like. Too often they meet business owners
      who assume they're being lied to when told what they <em>should</em> be paying.
      Changing that is the whole point.
    </p>

    <figure class="mt-8 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-rule">
      <img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dsbllwpbh/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/mwc/images/photos/truck-logo" alt="The Midwest Waste crew with a branded collection truck" class="aspect-[3/2] w-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption class="bg-steel px-4 py-3 text-sm text-muted">On the route in the Fox Valley.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-extrabold text-navy">The bear and the sphere</h2>
    <p class="text-muted">
      You've seen our trucks. The bear pushing the sphere isn't just a logo — it's
      the job. Strength, persistence, and momentum: moving heavy things forward,
      reliably, every day. It's the most recognizable mark in the Fox Valley waste
      business, and it stands for an old-fashioned promise — show up, do the work,
      stand behind it.
    </p>

    <figure class="mt-6 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-rule">
      <img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dsbllwpbh/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/mwc/images/photos/branded-frontloads" alt="Front-load dumpsters wearing the Midwest Waste bear-and-sphere logo" class="aspect-[3/2] w-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
      <figcaption class="bg-steel px-4 py-3 text-sm text-muted">The mark in the field — on every container we run.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2 class="mt-10 text-2xl font-extrabold text-navy">The anti-Waste-Management</h2>
    <p class="text-muted">
      Big national haulers are good at one thing: being big. You become an account
      number, your rate creeps every year, and getting a human on the phone is a
      project. We're the opposite by design. When you call, you talk to an owner.
      When you have a problem, the person you reach can fix it. That's not a
      marketing line — it's the entire reason we exist.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- VALUES -->
  <section class="bg-steel">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6 py-16">
      <span class="eyebrow">What We Stand For</span>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-extrabold text-navy">Plainspoken. Experienced. Direct.</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-5 sm:grid-cols-3">
        {
          [
            ["Strength", "The muscle behind hands-on hauling and three decades of operational know-how."],
            ["Momentum", "We move things forward — for the route and for your bottom line."],
            ["Trust", "High-contrast honesty. Speak to an owner, get a straight answer."],
          ].map(([t, d]) => (
            <div class="rounded-2xl border-l-4 border-orange bg-white p-6">
              <h3 class="font-display text-lg font-bold text-navy">{t}</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">{d}</p>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CtaBand />
</Layout>
